==English==
===Etymology===
From Indo-European root ''*bhle-'', to thrive or bloom, via {{OE.}} ''[[blostma]]''

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#Collectively, [[flower]]s on [[tree]]s.
#A single flower on a tree.

